text: Too often trauma bonding is mistaken for love. Honestly, most of us have never really experienced real love from another or struggle to love yourself because you don’t know what real love is. God is love. If God is absent, then it isn’t love. Please learn the difference.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Never get too comfortable with the goodness of your life that you start to take it for granted. This includes people and things. God always has a way of reminding us that in a split second it can all be undone. This is also why you’re supposed to appreciate the highs and lows.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Imagine thinking you’re a prize just because you have money. A prize is considered special because it’s usually earned not by just anybody. Mfs be giving themselves out FOR FREE to the needy. Ain’t no prize in that lol Birds of a feather flock together. That’s why I be solo.

author: Empress JaShada
text: When the desire for something better becomes stronger than your lack of discipline, you will develop discipline.

author: Empress JaShada
text: As much as you acknowledge the “bad” acknowledge the good as well if not more. It’s all for good reason.

author: Empress JaShada
text: -because you are made better by fighting through things meant to destroy you if that is what you choose to believe. Ask yourself this, are you better now than what you were? The evidence of your life now is a reflection of that.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Think about it…had we not experienced some of the things we have, would we be who we are? In the moments when life is happening it can be hard to accept certain things but one day you will look back -not from a victim standpoint- but from a victorious standpoint.

author: Empress JaShada
text: As f*cked up as some of the things we have and will experience in our lives, we can bring balance to those experiences that cause us a great deal of pain by also acknowledging the better person we become given that we choose to become better.

author: Empress JaShada
text: The way someone treats you will always have more to do with them than it will ever have to do with you. Just think about it…would you mistreat someone just because? It can still be hurtful but can you imagine the suffering they must feel inside that it projects outwardly…

author: Empress JaShada
text: They say that all money isn’t good money and I’ve learned that’s a fact. Some shit just isn’t worth it regardless of what’s being offered. Protect your energy at all costs.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Those bothered people usually want something for nothing. Regardless of the reason, that’ll never happen -long term- with someone like me. Once I sense that energy about you, I wouldn’t even want your business. It’s not worth the negative energy that will come with it.

author: Empress JaShada
text: If I put a price tag on anything related to me, please know the energy that you’re getting should be considered an investment because I almost always over deliver because that’s just my nature. But there has to be some type of exchange and that depends on what’s being offered.

author: Empress JaShada
text: And when that boost of power wears off, you think you can just come back and get some more. Especially if it’s making you better for other people. Not for free you can’t. I’ve known the power I hold for a while now and it’s something money can’t buy.

author: Empress JaShada
text: I’ve noticed how it really bothers [insecure] people when you’re an unbothered person. Some of us just choose to invest our power into ourselves because we are our biggest return on investment. I refuse to give my power away to anyone that will just take it and run.

author: Empress JaShada
text: And you can run but you can’t hide. Once you’ve had a taste of truth and authenticity, there’s no going back no matter how hard you try. No matter what it looks like on the outside. Your inside will always be at war if you choose to live outside of that. It’s best to embrace it.

author: Empress JaShada
text: Running into an evolved Libra is gonna always tug at that mask. We are the sign of justice. We (usually unintentional) make you face your truth because of our authentic nature of diplomacy. It will rub off or will have some type of effect on you if you stick around long enough.

author: Empress JaShada
text: You can learn to live authentically with your shadows. We all have them. Some may be darker than others but “above all, don’t lie to yourself.”

author: Empress JaShada
text:
“Above all, don’t lie to yourself.” 

It takes a certain kind of courageousness to really face your deepest darkest shadows. So many people’s authenticity is locked in cages or hidden behind a mask. Maybe in good reason. But I always feel the truth shall set you free.
